00:27:00.856 --> 00:27:02.810
So basically the
inspiration started

00:27:02.810 --> 00:27:05.890
is, I was in New
York City, where

00:27:05.890 --> 00:27:07.800
the runway shows are basically.

00:27:07.800 --> 00:27:12.464
So I was at ABC Carpets, which
is one of my favorite stores.

00:27:12.464 --> 00:27:14.380
If you're ever in New
York, you have to visit.

00:27:14.380 --> 00:27:17.450
But it's basically furniture,
carpets, accessory, everything.

00:27:17.450 --> 00:27:19.470
And it's curated in
such a beautiful way.

00:27:19.470 --> 00:27:20.760
I was so inspired.

00:27:20.760 --> 00:27:22.470
And so I went to
the fifth floor.

00:27:22.470 --> 00:27:26.010
And there's amazing rugs.

00:27:26.010 --> 00:27:30.530
They're either rugs done from
Eastern Europe, Persia, Turkey,

00:27:30.530 --> 00:27:32.380
all over the world basically.

00:27:32.380 --> 00:27:34.970
And what they do is
they take-- and they're

00:27:34.970 --> 00:27:36.920
the most gorgeous
colors you've ever seen.

00:27:36.920 --> 00:27:39.010
And they look familiar.

00:27:39.010 --> 00:27:42.210
They look like the
are traditional rugs.

00:27:42.210 --> 00:27:43.420
But they're are not.

00:27:43.420 --> 00:27:45.950
And I was so impressed
with the process.

00:27:45.950 --> 00:27:47.990
So I googled it.

00:27:47.990 --> 00:27:50.370
And it's called Color Reform.

00:27:50.370 --> 00:27:53.195
And what they do is they take
carpets that are damaged.

00:27:53.195 --> 00:27:55.830
So carpets that perhaps are
not so great or carpets that

00:27:55.830 --> 00:27:57.660
didn't make it to "A grade."

00:27:57.660 --> 00:28:00.770
And they bleach them,
dry them in the sun,

00:28:00.770 --> 00:28:02.040
and they redye them.

00:28:02.040 --> 00:28:04.290
And each carpet
is one of a kind.

00:28:04.290 --> 00:28:06.930
And I thought that
was so innovative.

00:28:06.930 --> 00:28:11.020
Anything, whether it's
in fashion or in tech,

00:28:11.020 --> 00:28:13.270
what makes a company
successful is passion, vision,

00:28:13.270 --> 00:28:14.780
and innovation.

00:28:14.780 --> 00:28:16.840
And they have done this
with these carpets,

00:28:16.840 --> 00:28:19.910
where each artist
puts passion into it.

00:28:19.910 --> 00:28:22.139
The innovation is
how they're done it.

00:28:22.139 --> 00:28:23.430
It's just such a great process.

00:28:23.430 --> 00:28:25.280
So anyway, I was
obsessed with it.

00:28:25.280 --> 00:28:29.340
So I took pictures, tons
of pictures of the carpets.

00:28:29.340 --> 00:28:32.490
And the prints that
you're going to see here

00:28:32.490 --> 00:28:35.650
are actually done
from the carpet kind

00:28:35.650 --> 00:28:36.860
of pictures and inspiration.

00:28:36.860 --> 00:28:38.600
So we did graphic
design, obviously,

00:28:38.600 --> 00:28:40.450
and printed it on silk.

00:28:40.450 --> 00:28:44.640
And then the other inspiration
was we're in California.

00:28:44.640 --> 00:28:47.270
So it's about sort
of bohemian spirit.

00:28:47.270 --> 00:28:49.070
It's about women--
like, I wanted

00:28:49.070 --> 00:28:52.800
her to just feel so
beautiful, elegant, and airy.

00:28:52.800 --> 00:28:57.030
And I just wanted that
bohemian side to come through.

00:28:57.030 --> 00:28:59.100
And then on the third
note, my daughter

00:28:59.100 --> 00:29:03.360
just got married,
actually last week.

00:29:03.360 --> 00:29:06.510
So it was such a beautiful
event, I have to tell you.

00:29:06.510 --> 00:29:08.250
She was she was stunning.

00:29:08.250 --> 00:29:13.800
And, yeah, it was
quite emotional.

00:29:13.800 --> 00:29:16.220
So when we were working
on this collection,

00:29:16.220 --> 00:29:18.400
I kept on thinking
so this is everybody

00:29:18.400 --> 00:29:20.344
that's walking down the aisle.

00:29:20.344 --> 00:29:21.180
[LAUGHTER]

00:29:21.180 --> 00:29:22.870
The whole party,
this is how I want.

00:29:22.870 --> 00:29:24.230
That's the finale that
you're going to see.

00:29:24.230 --> 00:29:25.710
But that's how I want everybody.

00:29:25.710 --> 00:29:27.140
Of course, that's not
what ended up happening.

